This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of machine learning (cs.LG) as it proposes a novel active learning algorithm for managing unlabeled datastream. It also involves optimization techniques, which could fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The application of the proposed algorithm to anomaly detection in healthcare and finance suggests that it could also be relevant to computer vision (cs.CV) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
